 frameworks.\\\" It seems we need to set up environment or system properties and other test-code setups in the agent guidance. A deterministic setup might need the org.slf4j dependency, but if it's only advisory, we could skip dependencies. The driver can apply deterministic dependencies or Docker, while system properties would need agent coding. I’ll aim for a verbosity level of 5.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker service is required for meaningful JGroups coverage, but tests should pin JGroups networking to loopback/IPv4 so local channel/protocol-stack coverage is stable in CI and native-image runs.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set JVM and native-test runtime system properties `jgroups.bind_addr=127.0.0.1` and `java.net.preferIPv4Stack=true`. Prefer local/loopback protocol-stack tests such as `JChannel`, XML/programmatic stacks, `SHARED_LOOPBACK`, or UDP bound to loopback; avoid requiring real multicast, DNS/cloud discovery, an external JDBC database, or cross-host networking. If logging is exercised, prefer the built-in JDK logging path unless the test intentionally verifies a custom `jgroups.log_class`.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"JGroups includes optional integrations such as SLF4J/log4j and WildFly OpenSSL, but the artifact POM marks logging backends optional and the documentation describes OpenSSL as optional; do not add them unless the generated tests specifically target that optional path.\",\n    \"Protocols such as `JDBC_PING`, DNS/cloud discovery, TCP gossip, and multicast can require external infrastructure or host networking if tested literally; generated tests should use in-memory/load-only substitutes or local loopback configurations.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0404183ef9300fca016a4277505b848190be1d6984c19661cf\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 479, "output": 617, "cacheRead": 48128, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49224, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782740808245, "responseId": "resp_0404183ef9300fca016a42774981c48190a94d54d8d915cf3d"}}
